This paper discusses the use of allocation strategies to improve the efficiency of crowdsourcing, which is a common topic in the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new method for performing inference on crowdsourcing data, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential bias introduced by allocation strategies, which is a topic in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of synthetic data to test the proposed method, which is a topic in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and modeling, which is a topic in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
